div.p:
And vvhat Child legitimate can vvith Patience brooke, that his Mother most Honourable, Chast, & Faythfull to her Spouse, should be accused and iudged for an Infamous Adultresse? No very Minister so ignorant, but vvill acknovvledge, that the Romane Church vvas the most chast & faythfull Spouse of Christ, vvhen S. Paul proclaymed that Rom. 1.8. her Fayth vvas renovvned in the vvhole vvorld: And Rom. 16.19. her obedience published into euery place: and the Romanes highly commended, for that
they had Rom. 6.17. obeyed from the hart, vnto that forme of doctrine vvhich had beene deliuered vnto them. And yet novv our viperous brood of Ministers, vvil needs haue her to be the very vvhore of Babylon;
Apoc. 17 a harlot &c. vvith vvhome the Kings of the Earth haue fornicated: An Apostata from Christ her Spouse; a profaner of Gods vvord and Sacraments and in briefe, vvholy Antichristian.
